{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"NAM","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Nahum"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Nahum"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Nahum"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Nahum"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Nahum"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Burden against Nineveh"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../jonah/1.htm|>Jonah 1:1–3</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"This is the burden against Nineveh, the book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The LORD is a jealous and avenging God; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the LORD is avenging and full of wrath. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The LORD takes vengeance on His foes "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" and reserves wrath for His enemies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The LORD is slow to anger "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and great in power; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the LORD will by no means "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["leave the guilty unpunished . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["His path is in the whirlwind and storm, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and clouds are the dust beneath His feet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"He rebukes the sea and dries it up; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He makes all the rivers run dry. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Bashan and Carmel wither, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the flower of Lebanon wilts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The mountains quake before Him, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the hills melt away; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the earth trembles at His presence— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the world and all its dwellers . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Who can withstand  His indignation? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Who can endure His burning anger ? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["His wrath is poured out like fire; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["even rocks are shattered before Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The LORD is good, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a stronghold in the day of distress; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He cares for those who trust in Him. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But with an overwhelming flood "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will make an end of Nineveh ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>of her place</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and pursue His enemies into darkness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Whatever you plot against the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He will bring to an end. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Affliction will not rise up "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a second time. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For they will be entangled as with thorns "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and consumed like the drink of a drunkard —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like stubble that is fully dry. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"From you, O Nineveh, comes forth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a plotter of evil against the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a counselor of wickedness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"This is what the LORD says: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Though they are allied  and numerous, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["yet they will be cut down and pass away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Though I have afflicted you, O Judah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will afflict you no longer. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"For I will now break their yoke from your neck "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and tear away your shackles. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The LORD has issued a command concerning you, O Nineveh: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There will be no descendants "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to carry on your name . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will cut off the carved image and cast idol "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the house of your gods; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will prepare your grave, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you are contemptible. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Look to the mountains— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the feet of one who brings good news, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who proclaims peace! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Celebrate your feasts, O Judah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["fulfill your vows. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For the wicked will never again  march through you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they will be utterly cut off. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Overthrow of Nineveh"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"One who scatters advances "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["against you, O Nineveh. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Guard the fortress! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Watch the road! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Brace yourselves ! ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>Strengthen your loins!</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Summon all your strength! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"For the LORD  will restore the splendor of Jacob "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like the splendor of Israel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["though destroyers have laid them waste "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and ruined the branches of their vine. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The shields of his mighty men are red; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the valiant warriors  are dressed in scarlet. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The fittings of the chariots flash like fire "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["on the day they are prepared, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the spears of cypress "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["have been brandished. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew; alternately, the spears may be of <i>pine</i> or <i>juniper</i> or <i>fir</i>; LXX and Syriac <i>they are prepared, and the horsemen rush to and fro.</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"The chariots dash through the streets; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they rush around the plazas, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["appearing like torches, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["darting about like lightning. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He summons his nobles; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they stumble as they advance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They race to its wall; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the protective shield is set in place. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The river gates are thrown open "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the palace collapses. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"It is decreed that the city be exiled "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and carried away; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["her maidservants moan like doves, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and beat upon their breasts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Nineveh has been like a pool of water "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["throughout her days, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but now it is draining away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Stop! Stop!” they cry, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but no one turns back. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Plunder the silver! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Plunder the gold! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There is no end to the treasure, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["an abundance of every precious thing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"She is emptied! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yes , she is desolate and laid waste! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Hearts melt, knees knock, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["bodies tremble, and every face  grows pale ! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Where is the lions’ lair "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or the feeding ground  of the young lions, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["where the lion and lioness  prowled with their cubs, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with nothing to frighten them away? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The lion mauled enough for its cubs "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and strangled prey for the lioness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["It filled its dens with the kill, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and its lairs with mauled prey. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Behold, I am against you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD of Hosts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will reduce your chariots to cinders, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the sword will devour your young lions. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will cut off your prey from the earth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the voices of your messengers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will no longer be heard . "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Judgment on Nineveh"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Woe to the city of blood, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["full of lies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["full of plunder, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["never without prey. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"The crack of the whip, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the rumble  of the wheel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["galloping horse "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and bounding chariot! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Charging horseman, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["flashing sword, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["shining spear; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["heaps of slain, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["mounds of corpses, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["dead bodies without end— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they stumble over their dead— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"because of the many harlotries of the harlot, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" the seductive mistress of sorcery, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who betrays nations by her prostitution "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and clans by her witchcraft. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Behold, I am against you, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["declares the LORD of Hosts. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will lift your skirts over your face. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will show your nakedness to the nations "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your shame to the kingdoms. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"I will pelt you with filth "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and treat you with contempt; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I will make a spectacle of you. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then all who see you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["will recoil from you and say, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Nineveh is devastated; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who will grieve for her? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Where can I find "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["comforters for you? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Are you better than Thebes , ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>No-amon</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["stationed by the Nile with water around her, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whose rampart was the sea, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["whose wall was the water? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Cush ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the upper Nile region"]}],"caller":"+"},"and Egypt were her boundless  strength; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Put and Libya were her allies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Yet she became an exile; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["she went into captivity. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Her infants  were dashed to pieces "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["at the head of every street. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They cast lots for her dignitaries, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and all her nobles were bound in chains. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"You too will become drunk; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["you will go into hiding  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and seek refuge from the enemy. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"All your fortresses are fig trees "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with the first ripe figs; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["when shaken, they fall "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["into the mouth of the eater! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Look at your troops —  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they are like your women ! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The gates of your land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["are wide open  to your enemies; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["fire consumes their bars. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Draw your water for the siege; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["strengthen your fortresses. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Work the clay and tread the mortar; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["repair the brick kiln! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"There the fire will devour you; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the sword will cut you down "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and consume you like a young locust. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Make yourself many like the young locust; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["make yourself many like the swarming locust! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"You have multiplied your merchants "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["more than the stars of the sky. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The young locust strips the land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and flies away. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Your guards ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>princes</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"are like the swarming locust, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and your scribes ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>marshals</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"like clouds of locusts  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that settle on the walls on a cold day. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When the sun rises, they fly away, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and no one knows  where. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"O king of Assyria, your shepherds slumber; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your officers sleep. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Your people are scattered on the mountains "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with no one to gather them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"There is no healing for your injury; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your wound is severe. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["All who hear the news of you "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["applaud  your downfall, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for  who has not experienced "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["your constant cruelty? "]}]}